//CAVERN
  "CavernMsg1": "It's an old, abandoned cottage.",
  "CavernMsg2": "The boards are nailed down tightly; they aren't budging.",
  "CavernMsg3": "The fishing rod is stuck in the mud.",
  "CavernMsg4": "It's an old book. You reach out to pick it up, but it begins to crumble at your touch. You decide to leave it where it is.",
  "CavernMsg5": "The fish are petrified and have a strange, stone-like quality to them.",
  "CavernMsg6": "The map reads 'The Great Wizard Norefundus presents: The Cunning Caverns Conundrum! A treasure hunt for adventurers of all skill levels!'.#It's covered in some rather questionable stains... you probably shouldn't touch it.", 
  "CavernLetter1": "TRAVEL HUB & SPELL ROOM.",
  "CavernLetter2": "SPRING 27^^That fraud! I knew he was up to something when he sold me this map for such a low price; I can't find a thing!^^Ugh, my stomach doesn't feel good. I don't think I should have eaten those mushrooms... maybe I can find a use for this map after all...",
  "CavernDialogueCarl": "Carl: How ya doin'? Ah, these must be Robin's blueprints for the cottage interior; thanks!#Carl: There's some mighty fine timber here; not seen craftsmanship like this in decades! Real shame Robin is missing out though.#Carl: Phobias are funny things, ain't they?! You should hear me scream for my wife when I see a spider!#Carl: Anyhoo, I'll have this fixed up for ya in no time!",
  "CavernDialogueCarl2": "Carl: Everything should be all finished by tomorrow morning.",
 
//TRAVEL HUB
  "TravelHubMsg1": "It's an angry letter of resignation, peppered with a shocking amount of profanity.",
  "TravelHubMsg2": "Strange liquids seem to shimmer as the light catches the bottles.",
  "TravelHubMsg3": "You glimpse the leather-bound grimoire. The title reads 'Magical Manipulations of the Space-Time Continuum'.#The content of the book is completely illegible.",
  "TravelHubMsg4": "This candle seems odd. You are compelled to stare into the heart of the potassium flame...#You feel your senses slipping away and you become overwhelmed by the urge to laugh maniacally!",
  "TravelHubLetter1": "WARP ROOM^^Warps statues 1-4 will appear here automatically once you have discovered certain areas in the Caverns. You will receive an on-screen message updating you whenever a new warp appears here.^^Warps 5-6 will only appear if you have 'The Forgotten Woods' mod installed.",
  "TravelHubLetter2": "EMPLOYEE REMINDER^^Only staff that have worked in level 5 of the mines or below may be permitted use of the company elevator.",
  "TravelHubLetter3": "Mwahahahaha! Only a few steps away from total world domination!^^The mine collapse created the perfect miasma of dark energies for my masterpiece... there's so much anguish here; it's positively delicious! The incantations have been spoken, the warps are prepared and the appropriate ancient rituals have been performed; not too long to wait now.^^Ugh, I would have completed this soooo much sooner if the blasted minions didn't keep quitting; I mean really, as if they expected to be paid for their shoddy work... HA! You just can't get the staff these days.^^Something is finally happening...^WHAT?!^NO!^Why am I still writing?!^^AHHHHHHHHHH.......",
  "TravelHubMinecart": "The Forgotten Caverns (Travel Hub)",

//SPELL ROOM
  "SpellRoomMsg1": "It's' a terrarium filled with strange glowing plants.",
  "SpellRoomMsg2": "'Forgotten Fungi: Chapter 11'#'Parasols of Yoba are great glowing mushrooms rarely found in dark and ancient Caverns...'#'Steeped in old magics, they were cultivated by a long-forgotten sect of Yoba worshipers to enable vast quantities of flora growth where none should naturally exist'.",
  "SpellRoomMsg3": "'Galdoff's Guide to Ghostly Etiquette'#'When looking to befriend folks of the undead persuasion, it is a dreadful faux pas to gift them anything edible.'#'The only exception to this rule is any variation of tea; the rising steam from the leafy-liquid appears to offer comfort to their lost souls.'#'A certain way to gain a poltergeist-pal is via an offering of minerals or gemstones, the sparkle of which seem to evoke an enthralled quality within the life-challenged amongst us.'",
  "SpellRoomMsg4": "The grimoire is sealed shut. You take a closer look at the mounted jewel on the cover, within it you see a monstrous eye following your every move...",
  "SpellRoomLetter1": "Welcome to the Spell Room!^^Here you can cast spells to control forage amounts (green spell books), monsters numbers (red spell books) and monster types (purple spell books). ^^Read the posters behind the spell podiums to see what each spell changes, then touch the book podium to cast your required spell.^^The flashing signs in the Travel Hub will indicate what choices you currently have enabled.^^These spells only affect The Forgotten Caverns and will not have an effect anywhere else in Stardew Valley.",
  "SpellRoomLetter2": "LIMITED FORAGE^^This spell lowers the amount of forageable items that spawn in the Caverns.",
  "SpellRoomLetter3": "GENEROUS FORAGE^^This spell increases the amount of forageable items that spawn in the Caverns.",
  "SpellRoomLetter4": "ELIMINATE MONSTERS^^This spell removes all monsters from the Hot Springs and Catacombs, for an easier, more relaxed experience.^^Please note, even with this mode enabled, one of the secret areas will contain two monsters for story purposes.",
  "SpellRoomLetter5": "MANAGEABLE MONSTERS^^This spell spawns a lower, more manageable amount of monsters within the Hot Springs and Catacombs.",
  "SpellRoomLetter6": "MONSTER MADNESS^^This spell doubles the amount of monsters that can spawn in the Hot Springs and Catacombs.",
  "SpellRoomLetter7": "MUNDANE MONSTERS^^This spell spawns monsters that are appropriate for your combat level.",
  "SpellRoomLetter8": "MALEVOLENT MONSTERS^^This spell spawns 'Dangerous' varieties of monsters similar to those spawned during Qi's 'Danger in the Deep' and 'Skull Cavern Invasion' quests.",

//ORCHARD
  "OrchardMsg1": "It's a fully functional hot tub. The controls seem to be stuck, but there is a tiny message above them...#'Climb in to Soothe and Revitalize'.", 
  "OrchardMsg2": "A bottle of vintage Pinot Noir sits untouched and dust-covered on the small table.",
  "OrchardMsg3": "The towel has a pungent aroma of mildew and is clearly hosting a small hoard of insects within its folds.",
  "OrchardLetter1": "PRIVATE ORCHARD!^^Any mine employees caught trespassing will be terminated with immediate effect!^^P.S. This means ALL of you; keep OFF my property!^^Cassandra",
  "OrchardLetter2": "FALL 26^^I hate this place, but at least it's now beginning to feel tolerable! The cottage is FINALLY up to my exacting standards and the hot tub is definitely improving my mood... so what if I skim a little profit off the top for my comfort?! Corporate can afford it and what they don't know won't kill them.^^Bill's cough is worse, which concerns me. A drop in productivity may prompt headquarters to stick their beaks into my business; I simply can't have that! I think he has a son that will make a suitable replacement; not quite 'officially' old enough to mine yet... but rules can be bent and deals can be brokered.",

//HOT SPRINGS
  "HotSpringsMsg2": "The entrance is blocked... for now.#You should come back later.",
  "HotSpringsMsg3": "You glance inside the bag and discover a huge roach gorging itself on rotten fruit. You swiftly close the flap of the bag and leave your new friend to its fetid feast.",
  "HotSpringsMsg4": "The book appears to be a mining company logbook. You pick it up for a closer inspection and flip through its contents.#You see repeating pages of miner's clocking in and out times, the last of which was dated Winter 24, 150 years ago. There's a long list of people who clocked in and never left...",
  "HotSpringsLetter1": "CAVERNS CLUE 1^^A master of rod and tackle,^a lost-lord of scaly things,^he leaves behind his writings and the knowledge that it brings.",
  "HotSpringsLetter2": "CAVERNS CLUE 2^^Different from my kinsfolk,^yet still bathed in glowing light,^I dance upon a secret with my wings of gossamer night.",
  "HotSpringsLetter3": "CAVERNS CLUE 3^^The sorrowed-halls echo eons,^where all journeys reach their end,^yet clinging 'neath a lilypad,^you'll find a lifelong friend.",
  "HotSpringsLetter4": "CAVERNS CLUE 4^^An over-used trope;^tried, tested and true!^Behind nature's curtain,^a surprise waits for you...",
  "HotSpringsLetter5": "CAVERNS CLUE 5^^In a long-abandoned mine,^where employees toiled their last,^lies a long-forgotten worker,^with a gift from ages past.",
  "HotSpringsLetter6": "CAVERNS CLUE 6^^An avatar of my maker,^royal hue adorns my head.^I gaze upon a fool's alcove;^veiled secret of the dead.",
  "HotSpringsLetter7": "CAVERNS CLUE 7^^In an area that time forgot,^the greatest battle did transpire!^It's a tale of greedy pirates and of angry lizard fire.^^Their eggs, you see, were valued high,^so the pirates hatched a scheme,^forgetting that the dino's weren't as docile as they seem.^^Alas, the pirate's plot did fail,^and all remains is ash and smoke,^yet they left behind a shining prize;^just give their bones a poke!",
  "HotSpringsLetter8": "CAVERNS CLUE 8^^Amongst my fallen brethren,^where we once reached to greet covered skies,^I lie beneath the age-tattered reeds,^in my husk the youth survives.",
  "HotSpringsLetter9": "CAVERNS CLUE 9^^Follow the sacred symbol,^walk the cleric's faithful path,^where if thy mettle's judged pure and true,^you'll be gifted heaven's wrath.",
  "HotSpringsLetter10": "CAVERNS CLUE 10^^A foolish pirate's pension waits,^buried deep on an island shore.^As his hide was fried by a dinosaur pride,^he'll need his gold no more.",
  "HotSpringsLetter11": "EMPLOYEE REMINDER^^You need to get better at avoiding the steam cracks in the floor! I will not be issuing sick pay for your incompetence... in fact, I will dock a week's pay for anyone who has the audacity to complain to me about them again!^^Cassandra",

//GROTTO
  "GrottoLetter1": "DAY 6^We've been trapped in this grotto for what feels like forever; lured here by this idiotic treasure map! What we first assumed to be mermaids are in fact SIRENS... all too keen for the taste of our flesh. Their song has bewitched us and is preventing us from leaving. The strange glowing plants seem to keep them at bay, but my assistant's resolve weakens by the hour.^^^DAY 9^Well, my assistant is dead; they hurled themselves at the sirens with the voracity of a toddler towards a chocolate cake. The vixens have now begun taunting me and are hurling bones at my head...^... oh, but how beautiful they are... ",

//SANCTUM
  "SanctumMsg1": "An ancient prayer to Yoba is engraved on the brass plate.",
  "SanctumLetter1": "My time remaining is short and I fear I shall succumb to my battle wounds before nightfall.^^I have transferred what remains of my divine magics into my sword and secured it away, in the vain hope that I may yet assist in the fight against evil. Only the most fervent monster slayer; a true combat master, may claim my enchanted blade.^^My only wish is for this holy war to be over and for the valley to live in peace and tranquillity once more.^^Eliza^Divine Cleric of Yoba",

//FORGOTTEN MINE
  "MineMsg1": "A quick glance into the tunnel reveals this minecart is useless; there's a cave-in further along the tracks.",
  "MineMsg2": "You approach the fire. A sickly feeling of unease touches your skin where warmth should have been.",

//FORGOTTEN MINE REPAIRED
  "RepairedMineMsg1": "The minecart is still blocked in.",
  "RepairedMineMsg2": "This is where Bob has laid his friends to rest.",
  "RepairedMineMsg3": "'My Friends. May You Rest in Peace and Always Walk in the Sunshine, Wherever You Are'",

//FORGOTTEN RECYLING ROOM
"RecyclingRoomMsg1": "The gravestone simply says one word:'Cassandra'.#After all you've discovered about the mine supervisor, Bob's choice of resting location for her is rather appropriate.",

//WORKERS HUT
  "HutMsg1": "The lockers are rusted shut.",
  "HutMsg2": "A strong stench of rot emits from the tiny parcel.",
  "HutMsg3": "It's an old map depicting possible mining locations.",
  "HutMsg4": "You creek open a nearby cupboard and notice a troop of regimental insects weaving their way through the cracks in the wood.",
  "HutMsg5": "'Manoeuvring the Machinations of Machiavellian Managers'",
  "HutMsg6": "'How to Survive and Thrive in a Toxic Work Environment'",
  "HutMsg7": "You notice a pile of school text books on the floor. You open the top book and see Bob's name inked neatly onto the inside cover.",
  "HutMsg8": "It may be wearing a snazzy hat, but the skull's self-promotion is becoming a little shameless.#You roll your eyes and walk away.",
  "HutMsg9": "You contemplate sitting on the sofa, but you'd rather not give your farm animals fleas.",
  "HutMsg10": "The stools are rotten and crawling with mites.",
  "HutMsg11": "Oh, how delightfully creepy!",
  "HutMsg12": "It's a list of worker's names and nonsensical reasons for docking their pay.#Whoever wrote this list was not only petty, but utterly heartless too.",

//WORKERS HUT REPAIRED
  "BobHouseMsg1": "Bob's painting skills are really coming along!",
  "BobHouseMsg2": "The display is filled with a collection of sparkling gemstones and minerals.",
  "BobHouseMsg3": "Mirror, mirror, on the wall...",
  "BobHouseMsg4": "The plant box is filled with a selection of flora from the Caverns.",
  "BobHouseMsg5": "'Moving Mountains: A Guide to Mastering Telekinesis!'",
  "BobHouseMsg6": "'Galdoff's Guide to Ghostly Etiquette'#'When looking to befriend folks of the undead persuasion, it is a dreadful faux pas to gift them anything edible...'#'The only exception to this rule is any variation of tea; the rising steam from the leafy-liquid appears to offer comfort to their lost souls...'#'A certain way to gain a poultergheist-pal is via an offering of minerals or gemstones, the sparkle of which seem to evoke an enthralled quality in the life-challenged amongst us.'",
  "BobHouseMsg7": "'Distinguishing the Dead'#'Ghosts can be split into varying categories, the most noticeable of which being their appearance...'#'Ghosts with a strong sense of purpose and existence will retain their mortal features, appearing as they did in life...'#'Ghosts that have become overwrought with despair, losing their sense of self, appear as if covered with a heavy mourning shroud.",
  "BobHouseMsg8": "'Traversing the Afterlife'",
  "BobHouseMsg9": "'Yoba: Fact or Fiction?'",
  "BobHouseMsg10": "'The Tiny Book of Celtic Conundrums'",
  "BobHouseMsg11": "'Unravelling the Mysterium'",
  "BobHouseMsg12": "'The Wraith's Wrath'",
  "BobHouseMsg13": "'El Pollo Diablo: The Foulest Fowl'",
  "BobHouseMsg14": "Bob has made a small shrine for the lost miners.",
  "BobHouseLetter1": "Feel free to use my kitchen anytime you like! It's not like I'm going to use it... but it didn't feel right to have a home without one.  ^   -Bob",

//CATACOMBS
  "CatacombsMsg1": "The skeletal remains of a pirate lie at your feet. A faint aroma of smoke is wafting through the small hole nearby.#You peer towards the crevice... it looks large enough to fit through...",
  "CatacombsMsg2": "The flickering blue flame offers no warmth, yet it leaves you feeling strangely comforted.",
  "CatacombsMsg3": "You try to remove the skull's hat but it's stuck tight. You can't explain how, but you swear it just winked at you!#The skull stares knowingly towards the alcove to the right.",
  "CatacombsMsg4": "The gate is locked... for now.",
  "CatacombsMsg5": "The gate is locked.#If you'd like to access this area and continue the creepy fun, head to nexusmods.com and download 'The Forgotten Woods'.",
  "CatacombsLetter1": "^^When wounds of loss lie open, when sorrow fills comfort's stead,^take solace in my words to come, let no more tears be shed.^^My light will always find you when you fall into dark abyss.^Recall my touch, my laugh, my love; memories death cannot dismiss.^^ ^^Lament no more, I beseech you; recall me with joy and song,^for remember that I'm still with you, side-by-side, forever long. [letterbg Mods/Azathii.TheForgottenCaverns/Azathii_LBGravestone 0][textcolor white]",

//SPEAKEASY
  "SpeakeasyMsg1": "You try to greet the skeleton with a smile, but he turns his head away from you in disgust.#You get the feeling that the living aren't that welcome here.",
  "SpeakeasyMsg2": "You aren't quite sure why, but the snail reminds you of that one aunt during the holidays...",
  "SpeakeasyMsg3": "'Handbook For The Recently Deceased' .This book seems vaguely familiar...#...you feel the urge to say a peculiar name three times. ",
  "SpeakeasyMsg4": "It's a magazine called 'RIP Weekly'. Curiosity gets the better of you and you flip through some of the pages...#'10 Ways To Discover If Your Mummy Is All Wrapped Up In You'...#'Lycan Lifestyle: Does Trimming Really Make Your Tail Look Longer?...#'Still Trying To Lose Those Last Few Pounds? Trust Mourningwood(TM) Brand Maggots! Your Bones Picked Clean or Your Money Back (T&C's Apply)...#You eagerly place the magazine back down. There's no accounting for taste, even in the afterlife.",
  "SpeakeasyMsg5": "You pat the skeletal wolf on the head and feel a bony snout nuzzle kindly into your leg.#Well, at least someone likes you here...",
  "SpeakeasyMsg6": "This table is occupied.",
  "SpeakeasyMsg7": "'A human that performs great evil in their lifetime will often become a 'soul-void' skeleton in death.#These foul creatures seek nothing more than to destroy the living, often found stalking innocent farmers throughout icy biomes and haunted crypts.'",
  "SpeakeasyMsg10": "A small note is stuffed between the books: 'Have you seen the handy-work of that crackpot old wizard near the surface? The insufferable fool blew himself up with his idiotic machinations.'",
  "SpeakeasyMsg11": "The skeleton lowers his newspaper and raises his head to meet your gaze.#The smouldering purple flames in his eye sockets seem to radiate pure annoyance.",
  "SpeakeasyMsg12": "The Pirate Captain is humming to himself.",
  "SpeakeasyLetter1": "Mr. Qi and the Calico Club proudly presents:^The Ghastly Games Room!^(Opening Soon)^^Fiendish fun for all foul creatures!",
  "SpeakeasyLetter2": "^^Breathless words can never portray the deafening depth of my dreams.^^Pray my pain be banished via ink and quill 'til reality pulls at its seams.",
  "SpeakeasySpeechIntoxS": "Intoxicated Skeleton: Meow! Hehe! *Hic*",
  "SpeakeasySpeechAnnoyS": "Annoyed Skeleton: Dave really needs to stop! If I hear one more bad joke, I'm going to feed him to the pit fiends!",
  "SpeakeasySpeechSketchS": "Grave Robber: Shhhh! Not so loud! Got some top-quality goods here... all hush-hush!#Grave Robber: You'd be amazed what you can find in people's graves... err... I mean 'casually lying around'.#Grave Robber: Check the crate... and stop looking so suspicious!",
  "SpeakeasySpeechImpatS": "Impatient Skeleton: That Qi guy was supposed to have this open by now! I've been waiting FOREVER!",

//VAULT
  "VaultMsg1": "Locked.",
  "VaultMsg2": "It's unwise to steal from the undead.",
  "VaultMsg3": "The icy stare of Edgar's raven makes chills run down your spine.",
  "VaultLetter1": "Due to repeated theft from gravesites, all valuables are to be stored here under the watch of Edgar's raven.",

//GAMES ROOM
  "GamesRoomMsg1": "You reach out to touch the statue. Within a split-second, the knight raises its sword and slams it into the ground!#Security seems to be taken rather seriously in here.",
  "GamesRoomMsg2": "Gambling Skeleton: Hey! That gold's mine! Keep your hands off.",
  "GamesRoomMsg3": "'The Gambler's Guide to Gold Galore!' by The Great Wizard, Norefundus.",
  "GamesRoomMsg4": "A few playing cards sit abandoned on the table.",
  "GamesRoomMsg5": "Some of Earl's concoctions have been left on the small table. The liquid in the bottles swirl around in an almost hypnotic pattern.",
  "GamesRoomMsg6": "STAFF ONLY!",
  "GamesRoomSpeechImpatS": "Impatient Skeleton: Finally; some entertainment around here!",
  "GamesRoomSpeechUnluckS": "Unlucky Skeleton: *Sigh* I never win anything!",
  "GamesRoomSpeechGambS": "Gambling Skeleton: Go away; I'm on a roll!",
  "GamesRoomSpeechPlayS": "Grateful Skeleton: It was so kind of Mr.Qi to open this for us... it was getting a little dull down here.",
  "GamesRoomSpeechObsS1": "Obsessed Skeleton: I'm going to get that Junimo plush, even if I have to sell my soul for it!#Obsessed Skeleton: I'm not moving until I get one.",
  "GamesRoomSpeechObsS2": "Obsessed Skeleton: It's finally mine!#Obsessed Skeleton: He's so FLUFFY!",
  "GamesRoomSpeechPoolS": "Relaxed Skeleton: Ahh! Nothin' like a lil' rest and relaxation to put life into these old bones.",
  "GamesRoomSpeechShopS": "Pondering Skeleton: I wonder what I'll buy with my winnings?",
  "GamesRoomSpeechReadS": "Skeptical Skeleton: This advice is utterly ridiculous; you'd be bankrupt within seconds! What a load of...",
  "GamesRoomSpeechLuckS": "Lucky Skeleton: I've won so many rounds that I'm now finding this a little boring.",

//WARPS
  "WarpHub": "WARP DESTINATION: Travel Hub (Caverns)", 
  "WarpOrchard": "WARP DESTINATION: Orchard (Caverns)",
  "WarpSprings": "WARP DESTINATION: Hot Springs (Caverns)",
  "WarpCatacombs": "WARP DESTINATION: Skeleton Speakeasy (Catacombs)",
  "WarpBasement": "WARP DESTINATION: Cottage Basement (Caverns)",
  "WarpWoodsShrine": "WARP DESTINATION: Forgotten Shrine (The Forgotten Woods)",
  "WarpWoodsFarm": "WARP DESTINATION: Forgotten Farm (The Forgotten Woods)",
  "Mincart": "Travel Hub (The Forgotten Caverns)",
  "DMTENewWarp": "A new warp has appeared in the Travel Hub.",
  "DMTEWoodsWarp": "You've unlocked new shortcut warps!#Warps to The Forgotten Caverns Travel Hub have appeared on the Forgotten Farm map (NE of the ruined farmhouse) and the Forgotten Shrine map (E of the treehouse).#Warps to both of these places have also appeared in the Travel Hub.",

//DMTE
  "DMTEForageLowSpawnOn": "You read the tome; the spell of 'Limited Forage' has been cast.#Caverns forage will spawn at a lower rate from 6am tomorrow onwards.",
  "DMTEForageHighSpawnOn": "You read the tome; the spell of 'Generous Forage' has been cast.#Caverns forage will spawn at a higher rate from 6am tomorrow onwards.",
  "DMTEMobNoSpawn": "You read the tome; the spell of 'Eliminate Monsters' has been cast.#Monsters will no longer spawn in the Hot Springs or Catacombs from 6am tomorrow onwards.",
  "DMTEMobNormalSpawn": "You read the tome; the spell of 'Manageable Monsters' has been cast.#Monsters in the Hot Springs and Catacombs will spawn at a regular rate from 6am tomorrow onwards.",
  "DMTEMobHighSpawn": "You read the tome; the spell of 'Monster Madness' has been cast.#Monsters in the Hot Springs and Catacombs will spawn at a higher rate from 6am tomorrow onwards.",
  "DMTEVanMob": "You read the tome; the spell of 'Mundane Monsters' has been cast.#Monsters appropriate to your combat level will spawn in the Hot Springs and Catacombs from 6am tomorrow onwards.",
  "DMTEDangMob": "You read the tome; the spell of 'Malevolent Monsters' has been cast.#Dangerous monsters will spawn in the Hot Springs and Catacombs from 6am tomorrow onwards.",
  "DMTECavernTreasure1": "The long-forgotten bag is covered with dirt and it smells like rotten fish guts. You hold your breath and glance inside...",
  "DMTECavernTreasure1Empty": "It's a rather dirty, empty bag. Just the thought of opening it back up makes you feel nauseous.",
  "DMTECavernTreasure2": "You peer into the rose bush and notice something strange. You gently guide your hand through the briar. After a rigorous search, and several nasty scratches, you find your prize.",
  "DMTECavernTreasure2Empty": "You briefly consider shoving your hand back into the gaping maw of the rosebush, then decide against it.",
  "DMTETravelHubWelcome": "Welcome to the Travel Hub!#Ahead of you is a minecart and the door to your left contains a room with a mine elevator.#The area to your right is the warp room; new warps will appear as you progress through the Caverns. Read the sign on the wall for more information.#The door to your far right contains the 'Spell Room'. In this area you can cast spells to alter the daily forage spawn rate, monster spawn rate and monster types within The Forgotten Caverns.#Have Fun!",
  "DMTETravelHubTreasure": "The wizard's eccentric hat catches your eye... yoink! ",
  "DMTETravelHubTreasureEmpty": "It's the hatless skull of a rather mad and cantankerous old wizard.",
  "DMTEOrchardTreasure": "Behind the reeds is a sunken old log. You plunge your hand into the water and inspect the hollowed cavity of the ancient tree.", 
  "DMTEOrchardTreasureEmpty": "It's a sunken, hollow log.", 
  "DMTEHotSpringsShrineHTrue": "You touch the Wild Shrine of the Hunter and receive a blessing.",
  "DMTEHotSpringsShrineHFalse": "HUNTER'S WILD SHRINE: When the sun is at its zenith, make offering at my shrine, be thee low or mighty hunter, my daily gifts be thine.",
  "DMTEHotSpringsShrineGTrue": "You touch the Wild Shrine of the Gatherer and receive a blessing.",
  "DMTEHotSpringsShrineGFalse": "GATHERER'S WILD SHRINE: When the sun is at its zenith, make offering at my shrine, be thee low or mighty gatherer, my daily gifts be thine.",
  "DMTEHotSpringsTreasure": "X marks the spot! You dig and discover the pirate's hidden stash.",
  "DMTEHotSpringsTreasureEmpty": "There's nothing here but dirt... and a few earthworms.",
  "DMTEGrottoTreasure": "The sirens call to you as you hastily dig. You seem curiously immune to their song...#... almost as if something, or someone, is protecting you...",
  "DMTEGrottoTreasureEmpty": "There's nothing useful in the crate. You can see tattered copies of the books 'Single and Ready to Mingle' and 'Adventuring Your Way to Romance' lying dog-eared and dust-covered at its base.",
  "DMTEGrottoTreasureEmpty2": "You've already dug up the treasure; there's nothing here. As you step away, you notice a siren flashing you a fang-toothed grin.",
  "DMTESanctumTreasure1": "Ooooo, Shiny! You gently, and very respectfully, loot the cleric's helm.",
  "DMTESanctumTreasure1Empty": "The cleric's skull stares lifelessly towards you.",
  "DMTESanctumTreasure2a": "You hear an ethereal voice: 'YOU MAY HAVE MY BLESSING, BUT YOU ARE NOT YET WORTHY OF MY BLADE'.",
  "DMTESanctumTreasure2b": "You hear an ethereal voice: 'YOU ARE WORTHY! HAVE MY BLADE AND BLESSING BOTH'.",
  "DMTESanctumTreasure2Empty": "It's an empty display case. The spirit no longer speaks to you, yet you feel their blessing surround you.",
  "DMTEMineTreasure1a": "You notice an impeccably-carved name on the skeleton's hat: 'Bob'. You curiously search around in the minecart for more information and pull out a rather smelly pair of cowboy boots.",
  "DMTEMineTreasure1aEmpty": "You don't want to disturb Bob's bones any further.",
  "DMTEMineTreasure1b": "You rummage around in the minecart and find an old pair of Cowboy Boots.",
  "DMTEMineTreasure1bEmpty": "There's nothing here but rubble and the faint smell of sweaty feet.",
  "DMTECatacombsSpiritTree": "You place your hand on the spirit tree. A familiar feeling of safety and warmth envelopes you, like a hug from a loved one who has since departed.",
  "DMTECatacombsFountain": "You toss a coin into the Fountain of Fates... you feel your luck has changed!",
  "DMTECatacombsTreasure1": "The lilypad catches your eye. You cautiously lift the watery leaf and discover a clutch of frog eggs.",
  "DMTECatacombsTreasure1Empty": "The lilypad is now empty. The remaining clutch must have washed away once you egg-napped their sibling.",
  "DMTECatacombsBox1": "A curious smell emanates from the small crate... you pry open the lid.",
  "DMTECatacombsBox1Empty": "It's an empty crate.",
  "DMTECatacombsInk": "You carefully pick up the quill and ink, wary of spilling the contents. You'd better return to them to Edgar in the Speakeasy.",
  "DMTEDinoDenCabinBlocked": "A magical barrier blocks your way into the ship. A vision of a skull wearing a purple hat floats into your head. The skull is staring towards an alcove...",
  "DMTEDinoDenTreasure1": "You search through the pile of charred bones and discover a hidden precious gem.",
  "DMTEDinoDenTreasure1Empty": "It's just a pile of smoke-stained bones. Unless you need some xylophone practice, there's nothing here of interest.",
  "DMTEDinoDenTreasure2": "Awww, you can't leave this little egg here all alone... yoink!",
  "DMTEDinoDenTreasure2Empty": "You look at the empty nest and feel a pang of guilt. You quickly snap back to reality and remember that the Pepper Rex's were trying to barbecue you to a crisp!#The guilty feeling swiftly passes.",
  "DMTECaptainsCabinLocket": "An ornate golden locket lies on the floor. You pick it up and peer inside...#You see a tiny portrait of a jovial pirate captain, surrounded by his smiling crew. You're sure you've seen this captain before...",
  "DMTECaptainsCabinLocketEmpty": "There's nothing here.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechSidA": "Sid: No death certificate; no service! Move along, fleshbag.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechSidB": "Sid: Don't take this as me approving of your presence here, but you've done well with the kid.#Sid: I'll tolerate you in my bar... for now.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechPetra.True": "Petra: Ah! I see you're a fellow would-be-perfectionist.#Petra: It was something I always strove for in life too.#Petra: Head to the vault; there's a little something in my chest that I think will help you out. Do keep up the good work, my dear.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechPetraA": "Petra: Oh, you don't really belong here, my dear; you have a full and rich life ahead of you.#Petra: In life I always strove for perfection. Once you begin to focus on that ethos for that yourself, come back and see me... I may have something for you.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechPetraB": "Petra: I see you're now tracking your perfection; it really is an excellent goal.#Petra: Head to the vault; there's a little something in my chest that I think will help you out.# Petra: Do keep up the good work, my dear.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechPetraC": "Petra: Hello again, my dear.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechWren.True": "Wren: I used to be an adventurer like you. Then I took an arrow in the knee...#Wren: The one I took to the head didn't exactly help things either.#Wren: Anyway, I always wanted to visit the Volacano Caldera on Ginger Island, but no-matter how hard I tried, I could never reach the top.#Wren: Oh, you've already visited the Caldera? It must have been wonderful!#Wren: I have something that I picked up on my last visit to the island; I never found a use for it, so you are more than welcome to it. You'll find it in my vault chest.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechWrenA": "Wren: I used to be an adventurer like you. Then I took an arrow in the knee...#Wren: The one I took to the head didn't exactly help things either.#Wren: Anyway, I always wanted to visit the Volacano Caldera on Ginger Island, but no-matter how hard I tried, I could never reach the top.#Wren: If you ever reach the top please come back and tell me about it; I'd love to hear about your travels.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechWrenB": "Wren: You've visited the Volacano Caldera? Thanks for telling me the tale of your travels; I only wish I'd have been there too!#Wren: I have something that I picked up on my last visit to the island; I never found a use for it, so you are more than welcome to it. You'll find it in my vault chest.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechWrenC": "Wren: I wish I could go on more adventures, but these old bones just aren't up to it anymore.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechEarlA": "Earl: Hmmm, it's still not right...#Earl: Oh, hey! I've got a little task for you. I need something to add a nice little 'kick' to my latest brew, but I can't find my spices.#Earl: I think Sid moved them somewhere nearby when he was cleaning this morning. Can you find them for me?",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechEarlB": "Earl: You found them!#Earl: Ah, wonderful! My spices are bringing the perfect balance to my concoction.#Earl: I've left a little something for you in the vault as my way of thanks.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechEarlC": "Earl: Now, was it four decades turning clockwise, or anti-clockwise?",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechEdgarA": "Edgar: Alas, my heart presently darkens and I find myself in the greatest of need. I wish to write a sonnet for my lost love, Lenore, yet I have lost my quill and Ink.#I must have mislaid them when I was taking my morning constitutional through the catacombs. Please find them so I can once again annotate my forlorn love.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechEdgarB": "Edgar: Ah, you've found my Ink! You have my thanks, mortal.#Edgar: My vault chest contains something I stumbled upon in my academic endevours; you are most welcome to it.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechEdgarC": "Edgar: Alone; my heart is ever alone.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechCaptainA": "The Pirate Captain ignores your presence whilst humming a sad sea shanty. You notice a scorched quality to his clothes and the scent of smoke lingers heavily upon him.#He looks so sad...",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechCaptainB": "The Pirate's humming has ceased.#His hands begin to tremble as he cautiously opens the tiny trinket. Time seems to halt for a few seconds as you watch him stare at the small painting within.#The captain carefully closes the locket, holds it against his chest and then tucks it into his coat pocket.#He turns his head towards the vault and offers you a silent but approving nod.",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechCaptainC": "The Captain is humming again, but you notice it is no longer his previous melancholic melody; it's a much more cheerful tune.", 
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave1": "Dave: Careful of our friend here... he gets a bit 'handsy' when he's drunk, Hehe!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave2": "Dave: How do you tell if a graveyard is infected?#Dave: Because everyone is coffin! Ah-hahaha!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave3": "Dave: What do you call an undead chicken?#Dave: A Poultry-geist!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave4": "Dave: Why don't skeletons skydive?#Dave: Because they don't have the guts!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave5": "Dave: What do you get if you cross a vampire and a snowman?#Dave: Frostbite!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave6": "Dave: Why shouldn't you tell secrets on a farm?#Dave: Because the potatoes have eyes and the corn have ears!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave7": "Dave: Why are ghosts bad liars?#Dave: They're too transparent!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave8": "Dave: Why are skeletons terrible pirates?#Dave: Because their chests are always empty!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave9": "Dave: I'll tickle your ribs, touch your funny bone and make your jaw drop with laughter...#Dave: Just call me the chiropractor of mirth!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave10": "Dave: What do you call an undead cleaner?#Dave: The Grim Sweeper!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave11": "Dave: Why are exorcists good at parties?#Dave: They lift people's spirits!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave12": "Dave: Why don't vampires like comedians?#Dave: They taste funny!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave13": "Dave: Why do farmers love comedians?#Dave: Because they have ears for corny jokes!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave14": "Dave: How do you tell if a farmer likes music?#Dave: They always turnip the beet!",
  "DMTESpeakeasySpeechDave15": "Dave: I've got a skele-TON of these jokes, you know!",
  "DMTEVaultChestPetraFalse": "Petra's chest is locked.",
  "DMTEVaultChestPetraTrue": "Petra's chest magically opens, floats the gems into your hand and re-locks itself.",
  "DMTEVaultChestWrenFalse": "Wren's chest is locked.",
  "DMTEVaultChestWrenTrue": "Wren's chest magically opens for you, allows you to take your gelatinous prize, then locks itself once more.",
  "DMTEVaultChestEarlFalse": "Earl's chest is locked.",
  "DMTEVaultChestEarlTrue": "Earl's chest magically opens for you, spits a pumpkin into your hands then locks itself again.",
  "DMTEVaultChestEdgarFalse": "Edgar's chest is locked.",
  "DMTEVaultChestEdgarTrue": "Edgar's chest magically opens for you, allows you to take a book, then snaps itself back shut.",
  "DMTEVaultChestCaptainFalse": "The Captain's chest is locked.",
  "DMTEVaultChestCaptainTrue": "The Captain's chest magically opens for you. You can faintly hear the ocean in the distance before the chest locks itself once more.",
  "DMTEGamesRoomSpices": "These look like Earl's missing spices. You hold a jar up to the light and see the distinctive outline of toenails and insect chitin. You gag a little and place the 'spices' safely into your bag.",
  "DMTEGamesRoomTreasure1": "You bend down to inspect the odd vending machine... there's something loose in here.",
  "DMTEGamesRoomTreasure1Empty": "The machine now appears to be out of order",
  "DMTELootTrue": "You've found something!",
  "DMTELootFalse": "It's empty.",
  "DMTEBerryTrue": "There's something in the branches.",
  "DMTEBerryTrueEmpty": "It's just a bush with inedible berries.",
  "DMTEBerryFalse": "The berries on this bush appear to be inedible.",
  "DMTEBarrelOre": "The barrel contains a large quantity of ore. You pick out any useful materials and leave only the flawed samples behind.",
  "DMTEBarrelOreEmpty": "Only poor-quality, flawed samples of ore remain here.",

